February 21 marks the 50th anniversary of then-president Richard Nixon's visit to China. Fifty years ago, far-sighted leaders from China and the U.S. decided to thaw the freezed relationship suspended over two decades. This important step opened up the path for the two countries and peoples to move toward all-round cooperation. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Michael Wang looks back on the 50 years of China-U.S. relations.